            "new_string": "<!-- ==================== MODULE 7: Web Search ==================== -->\n<section class=\"module\" id=\"module-7\">\n  <div class=\"module-content\">\n    <header class=\"module-header animate-in\">\n      <span class=\"module-number\">07</span>\n      <h1 class=\"module-title\">Giving the Agent Eyes</h1>\n      <p class=\"module-subtitle\">Web search and URL fetching — Phase 4</p>\n    </header>\n\n    <div class=\"screen animate-in\">\n      <h2 class=\"screen-heading\">Two new tools enter the arena</h2>\n      <p style=\"margin-bottom: var(--space-6);\">Phase 4 adds two <span class=\"term\" data-definition=\"A LangChain tool is a function the agent can decide to call. It has a name, description, and arguments schema.\">LangChain tools</span> to the agent's toolkit:</p>\n      <div class=\"pattern-cards stagger-children\">\n        <div class=\"pattern-card animate-in\" style=\"--stagger-index: 0; border-top: 3px solid var(--color-actor-2)\">\n          <div class=\"pattern-icon\" style=\"background: var(--color-actor-2)\">🔍</div>\n          <h4 class=\"pattern-title\">web_search</h4>\n          <p class=\"pattern-desc\">Calls the <strong>Tavily API</strong> with a query string. Returns a JSON list of results — each with title, URL, and a content snippet.</p>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"pattern-card animate-in\" style=\"--stagger-index: 1; border-top: 3px solid var(--color-actor-3)\">\n          <div class=\"pattern-icon\" style=\"background: var(--color-actor-3)\">🌐</div>\n          <h4 class=\"pattern-title\">fetch_url</h4>\n          <p class=\"pattern-desc\">Downloads a URL with <strong>httpx</strong>, converts the HTML to Markdown via <em>markdownify</em>, and truncates to 10,000 chars — so the agent can read web pages as text.</p>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"callout callout-info\" style=\"margin-top: var(--space-6)\">\n        <div class=\"callout-icon\">🔑</div>\n        <div class=\"callout-content\">\n          <strong class=\"callout-title\">Lazy credential injection</strong>\n          <p>Both tools read their API keys lazily — <code style=\"font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: var(--text-sm)\">TAVILY_API_KEY</code> is written into <code style=\"font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: var(--text-sm)\">os.environ</code> only when the agent first runs, not at import time. This means you can configure the TUI without importing the tools.</p>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"screen animate-in\">\n      <h2 class=\"screen-heading\">Why return JSON, not plain text?</h2>\n      <p style=\"margin-bottom: var(--space-6);\">Both tools return a <strong>JSON string</strong> — not a human-readable sentence. This is intentional.</p>\n      <div class=\"step-cards stagger-children\">\n        <div class=\"step-card animate-in\" style=\"--stagger-index: 0\">\n          <div class=\"step-num\">1</div>\n          <div class=\"step-body\">\n            <strong>Agent sees structured data</strong>\n            <p>The LLM can parse JSON and extract specific fields — title, URL, content — rather than guessing from prose.</p>\n          </div>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"step-card animate-in\" style=\"--stagger-index: 1\">\n          <div class=\"step-num\">2</div>\n          <div class=\"step-body\">\n            <strong>TUI widget recognises the format</strong>\n            <p><code style=\"font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: var(--text-sm)\">ToolCallMessage._format_web_output()</code> detects JSON with a <code style=\"font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: var(--text-sm)\">results</code> key and renders each result with a bold title and a dim URL — much richer than raw text.</p>\n          </div>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"step-card animate-in\" style=\"--stagger-index: 2\">\n          <div class=\"step-num\">3</div>\n          <div class=\"step-body\">\n            <strong>No double-formatting</strong>\n            <p>The widget is the single source of truth for display logic. The tool just provides the data; the widget decides how to show it. A single responsibility each.</p>\n          </div>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"screen animate-in\">\n      <h2 class=\"screen-heading\">The web search flow</h2>\n      <div class=\"step-cards stagger-children\">\n        <div class=\"step-card animate-in\" style=\"--stagger-index: 0\">\n          <div class=\"step-num\">1</div>\n          <div class=\"step-body\">\n            <strong>Agent emits <code style=\"font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: var(--text-sm)\">on_tool_start</code> with <code style=\"font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: var(--text-sm)\">name=\"web_search\"</code></strong>\n            <p>EventTranslator sees a normal tool name (not \"task\" or \"compact_conversation\"), so it yields a <code style=\"font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: var(--text-sm)\">TOOL_CALL</code> event.</p>\n          </div>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"step-card animate-in\" style=\"--stagger-index: 1\">\n          <div class=\"step-num\">2</div>\n          <div class=\"step-body\">\n            <strong>Adapter dispatches → approval widget</strong>\n            <p>The TUI shows the tool name and arguments. You decide: approve or deny.</p>\n          </div>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"step-card animate-in\" style=\"--stagger-index: 2\">\n          <div class=\"step-num\">3</div>\n          <div class=\"step-body\">\n            <strong>Approved → Tavily executes → <code style=\"font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: var(--text-sm)\">on_tool_end</code></strong>\n            <p>Results come back as JSON. EventTranslator yields <code style=\"font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: var(--text-sm)\">TOOL_RESULT</code>. The widget formats and displays them.</p>\n          </div>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"screen animate-in\">\n      <h2 class=\"screen-heading\">Quiz: Web tools</h2>\n      <div class=\"quiz-container\" id=\"quiz-7\">\n        <div class=\"quiz-question-block\" data-question=\"q1\" data-correct=\"option-b\">\n          <h3 class=\"quiz-question\">Why do <code style=\"font-family: var(--font-mono)\">web_search</code> and <code style=\"font-family: var(--font-mono)\">fetch_url</code> return JSON instead of a plain sentence like \"Here are the results\"?</h3>\n          <div class=\"quiz-options\">\n            <button class=\"quiz-option\" data-value=\"option-a\" onclick=\"selectOption(this)\">\n              <div class=\"quiz-option-radio\"></div>\n              <span>JSON is required by the Tavily API format</span>\n            </button>\n            <button class=\"quiz-option\" data-value=\"option-b\" onclick=\"selectOption(this)\">\n              <div class=\"quiz-option-radio\"></div>\n              <span>Both the LLM and the TUI widget can parse structured data reliably, while prose is ambiguous</span>\n            </button>\n            <button class=\"quiz-option\" data-value=\"option-c\" onclick=\"selectOption(this)\">\n              <div class=\"quiz-option-radio\"></div>\n              <span>JSON uses less tokens in the context window</span>\n            </button>\n          </div>\n          <div class=\"quiz-feedback\" id=\"q1-feedback\"></div>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"quiz-question-block\" data-question=\"q2\" data-correct=\"option-c\">\n          <h3 class=\"quiz-question\">When the agent calls <code style=\"font-family: var(--font-mono)\">web_search</code>, what happens first in the TUI?</h3>\n          <div class=\"quiz-options\">\n            <button class=\"quiz-option\" data-value=\"option-a\" onclick=\"selectOption(this)\">\n              <div class=\"quiz-option-radio\"></div>\n              <span>Tavily is called immediately with the query</span>\n            </button>\n            <button class=\"quiz-option\" data-value=\"option-b\" onclick=\"selectOption(this)\">\n              <div class=\"quiz-option-radio\"></div>\n              <span>The results are displayed in a formatted widget</span>\n            </button>\n            <button class=\"quiz-option\" data-value=\"option-c\" onclick=\"selectOption(this)\">\n              <div class=\"quiz-option-radio\"></div>\n              <span>An approval widget appears asking the user to allow or deny the search</span>\n            </button>\n          </div>\n          <div class=\"quiz-feedback\" id=\"q2-feedback\"></div>\n        </div>\n        <button class=\"quiz-check-btn\" onclick=\"checkQuiz('quiz-7')\">Check Answers</button>\n        <button class=\"quiz-reset-btn\" onclick=\"resetQuiz('quiz-7')\">Try Again</button>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n</section>\n\n<!-- ==================== MODULE 8: Planning & Subagents ==================== -->\n<section class=\"module\" id=\"module-8\">\n  <div class=\"module-content\">\n    <header class=\"module-header animate-in\">\n      <span class=\"module-number\">08</span>\n      <h1 class=\"module-title\">Agents Talking to Agents</h1>\n      <p class=\"module-subtitle\">Subagent spawning and planning events — Phase 5</p>\n    </header>\n\n    <div class=\"screen animate-in\">\n      <h2 class=\"screen-heading\">The \"task\" tool is special</h2>\n      <p style=\"margin-bottom: var(--space-6);\">When a DeepAgents agent needs to delegate work, it calls a tool named <code style=\"font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: var(--text-sm)\">task</code>. The TUI intercepts this before it ever reaches the approval widget.</p>\n      <div class=\"callout callout-accent\">\n        <div class=\"callout-icon\">🧠</div>\n        <div class=\"callout-content\">\n          <strong class=\"callout-title\">The interception pattern</strong>\n          <p>In <code style=\"font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: var(--text-sm)\">EventTranslator._handle_tool_start()</code>, the tool name is checked <em>before</em> the generic TOOL_CALL path. If the name is <code style=\"font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: var(--text-sm)\">\"task\"</code>, it yields <code style=\"font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: var(--text-sm)\">SUBAGENT_START</code> and returns early. The approval flow never fires.</p>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"pattern-cards stagger-children\" style=\"margin-top: var(--space-6)\">\n        <div class=\"pattern-card animate-in\" style=\"--stagger-index: 0; border-top: 3px solid var(--color-actor-4)\">\n          <div class=\"pattern-icon\" style=\"background: var(--color-actor-4)\">📋</div>\n          <h4 class=\"pattern-title\">PLAN_STEP</h4>\n          <p class=\"pattern-desc\">Agent is decomposing a task. Shows <strong>⚙ Planning N/M</strong> with the step text below it in the chat view.</p>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"pattern-card animate-in\" style=\"--stagger-index: 1; border-top: 3px solid var(--color-actor-5)\">\n          <div class=\"pattern-icon\" style=\"background: var(--color-actor-5)\">→</div>\n          <h4 class=\"pattern-title\">SUBAGENT_START</h4>\n          <p class=\"pattern-desc\">A subagent was spawned. Shows <strong>→ Subagent: &lt;name&gt;</strong> in the chat. Name comes from the <code style=\"font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: var(--text-sm)\">description</code> field, truncated to 80 chars.</p>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"pattern-card animate-in\" style=\"--stagger-index: 2; border-top: 3px solid var(--color-success)\">\n          <div class=\"pattern-icon\" style=\"background: var(--color-success)\">✓</div>\n          <h4 class=\"pattern-title\">SUBAGENT_END</h4>\n          <p class=\"pattern-desc\">Subagent finished. Shows <strong>✓ Subagent done: &lt;name&gt;</strong>. Emitted on <code style=\"font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: var(--text-sm)\">on_tool_end</code> with <code style=\"font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: var(--text-sm)\">name=\"task\"</code>, even when there's no output key.</p>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"screen animate-in\">\n      <h2 class=\"screen-heading\">Order matters: check the tool name first</h2>\n      <p style=\"margin-bottom: var(--space-6);\">A subtle bug was caught during implementation. Here's why the tool name check must happen <em>before</em> the output-presence guard:</p>\n      <div class=\"step-cards stagger-children\">\n        <div class=\"step-card animate-in\" style=\"--stagger-index: 0\">\n          <div class=\"step-num\" style=\"background: var(--color-error)\">✗</div>\n          <div class=\"step-body\">\n            <strong>Wrong order (original)</strong>\n            <p>Check if <code style=\"font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: var(--text-sm)\">\"output\" in data</code> → if missing, return early. <em>Then</em> check tool name. Result: if a task tool ends with no output key, SUBAGENT_END is silently dropped.</p>\n          </div>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"step-card animate-in\" style=\"--stagger-index: 1\">\n          <div class=\"step-num\" style=\"background: var(--color-success)\">✓</div>\n          <div class=\"step-body\">\n            <strong>Right order (fixed)</strong>\n            <p>Extract tool name first. If it's <code style=\"font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: var(--text-sm)\">\"task\"</code>, yield SUBAGENT_END and return — <em>regardless</em> of whether output is present. The output-presence guard only applies to regular tools.</p>\n          </div>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"callout callout-info\" style=\"margin-top: var(--space-4)\">\n        <div class=\"callout-icon\">💡</div>\n        <div class=\"callout-content\">\n          <strong class=\"callout-title\">The lesson</strong>\n          <p>When you have special cases that bypass generic logic, the special case check must come first. Early-return patterns are powerful — but only when the conditions are evaluated in the right order.</p>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"screen animate-in\">\n      <h2 class=\"screen-heading\">The subagent lifecycle in the TUI</h2>\n      <div class=\"step-cards stagger-children\">\n        <div class=\"step-card animate-in\" style=\"--stagger-index: 0\">\n          <div class=\"step-num\">1</div>\n          <div class=\"step-body\">\n            <strong>Agent emits <code style=\"font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: var(--text-sm)\">on_tool_start</code>, <code style=\"font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: var(--text-sm)\">name=\"task\"</code></strong>\n            <p>EventTranslator extracts the description (or task, or \"subagent\" as fallback), truncates to 80 chars, yields SUBAGENT_START.</p>\n          </div>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"step-card animate-in\" style=\"--stagger-index: 1\">\n          <div class=\"step-num\">2</div>\n          <div class=\"step-body\">\n            <strong>Adapter dispatches → <code style=\"font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: var(--text-sm)\">app.show_subagent_started(name)</code></strong>\n            <p>Status bar shows \"Running subagent: &lt;name&gt;\". Chat shows \"→ Subagent: &lt;name&gt;\" as an inline message.</p>\n          </div>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"step-card animate-in\" style=\"--stagger-index: 2\">\n          <div class=\"step-num\">3</div>\n          <div class=\"step-body\">\n            <strong>Subagent completes → <code style=\"font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: var(--text-sm)\">on_tool_end</code>, <code style=\"font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: var(--text-sm)\">name=\"task\"</code></strong>\n            <p>EventTranslator yields SUBAGENT_END. Adapter calls <code style=\"font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: var(--text-sm)\">show_subagent_finished</code>. Status bar resets to \"thinking\". Chat shows \"✓ Subagent done\".</p>\n          </div>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"screen animate-in\">\n      <h2 class=\"screen-heading\">Quiz: Subagents</h2>\n      <div class=\"quiz-container\" id=\"quiz-8\">\n        <div class=\"quiz-question-block\" data-question=\"q1\" data-correct=\"option-b\">\n          <h3 class=\"quiz-question\">When a DeepAgents agent spawns a subagent by calling the <code style=\"font-family: var(--font-mono)\">task</code> tool, does the TUI show the normal approval widget?</h3>\n          <div class=\"quiz-options\">\n            <button class=\"quiz-option\" data-value=\"option-a\" onclick=\"selectOption(this)\">\n              <div class=\"quiz-option-radio\"></div>\n              <span>Yes — all tool calls go through approval</span>\n            </button>\n            <button class=\"quiz-option\" data-value=\"option-b\" onclick=\"selectOption(this)\">\n              <div class=\"quiz-option-radio\"></div>\n              <span>No — the task tool is intercepted before reaching the approval flow and emits SUBAGENT_START instead</span>\n            </button>\n            <button class=\"quiz-option\" data-value=\"option-c\" onclick=\"selectOption(this)\">\n              <div class=\"quiz-option-radio\"></div>\n              <span>Only if the subagent uses dangerous tools</span>\n            </button>\n          </div>\n          <div class=\"quiz-feedback\" id=\"q1-feedback-8\"></div>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"quiz-question-block\" data-question=\"q2\" data-correct=\"option-a\">\n          <h3 class=\"quiz-question\">What happens if the <code style=\"font-family: var(--font-mono)\">on_tool_end</code> event for a <code style=\"font-family: var(--font-mono)\">task</code> tool has no <code style=\"font-family: var(--font-mono)\">output</code> key in its data?</h3>\n          <div class=\"quiz-options\">\n            <button class=\"quiz-option\" data-value=\"option-a\" onclick=\"selectOption(this)\">\n              <div class=\"quiz-option-radio\"></div>\n              <span>SUBAGENT_END is still emitted — the tool name check runs before the output-presence guard</span>\n            </button>\n            <button class=\"quiz-option\" data-value=\"option-b\" onclick=\"selectOption(this)\">\n              <div class=\"quiz-option-radio\"></div>\n              <span>The event is silently dropped</span>\n            </button>\n            <button class=\"quiz-option\" data-value=\"option-c\" onclick=\"selectOption(this)\">\n              <div class=\"quiz-option-radio\"></div>\n              <span>An error event is emitted instead</span>\n            </button>\n          </div>\n          <div class=\"quiz-feedback\" id=\"q2-feedback-8\"></div>\n        </div>\n        <button class=\"quiz-check-btn\" onclick=\"checkQuiz('quiz-8')\">Check Answers</button>\n        <button class=\"quiz-reset-btn\" onclick=\"resetQuiz('quiz-8')\">Try Again</button>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n</section>\n\n<!-- ==================== MODULE 9: Context Management ==================== -->\n<section class=\"module\" id=\"module-9\">\n  <div class=\"module-content\">\n    <header class=\"module-header animate-in\">\n      <span class=\"module-number\">09</span>\n      <h1 class=\"module-title\">Never Lose the Thread</h1>\n      <p class=\"module-subtitle\">Context compaction, token counting, and memory management — Phase 6</p>\n    </header>\n\n    <div class=\"screen animate-in\">\n      <h2 class=\"screen-heading\">The context window problem</h2>\n      <p style=\"margin-bottom: var(--space-6);\">Every LLM has a fixed context window. Long conversations fill it up. DeepAgents handles this automatically by calling a special tool — <code style=\"font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: var(--text-sm)\">compact_conversation</code> — to summarise old history. Phase 6 makes this visible in the TUI.</p>\n      <div class=\"pattern-cards stagger-children\">\n        <div class=\"pattern-card animate-in\" style=\"--stagger-index: 0; border-top: 3px solid var(--color-actor-2)\">\n          <div class=\"pattern-icon\" style=\"background: var(--color-actor-2)\">⏳</div>\n          <h4 class=\"pattern-title\">STATUS_UPDATE</h4>\n          <p class=\"pattern-desc\">Emitted when <code style=\"font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: var(--text-sm)\">compact_conversation</code> starts. Shows \"Compacting context…\" in the status bar so the user knows to wait.</p>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"pattern-card animate-in\" style=\"--stagger-index: 1; border-top: 3px solid var(--color-success)\">\n          <div class=\"pattern-icon\" style=\"background: var(--color-success)\">✓</div>\n          <h4 class=\"pattern-title\">CONTEXT_SUMMARIZED</h4>\n          <p class=\"pattern-desc\">Emitted when compaction ends. Carries the remaining token count parsed from the tool's JSON output. Mounts a <code style=\"font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: var(--text-sm)\">SummarizationMessage</code> in the chat and updates the status bar.</p>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"callout callout-info\" style=\"margin-top: var(--space-6)\">\n        <div class=\"callout-icon\">🔍</div>\n        <div class=\"callout-content\">\n          <strong class=\"callout-title\">Same interception pattern as subagents</strong>\n          <p>Just like the <code style=\"font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: var(--text-sm)\">task</code> tool bypasses the approval flow, <code style=\"font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: var(--text-sm)\">compact_conversation</code> is intercepted before reaching TOOL_CALL. The check runs before the <code style=\"font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: var(--text-sm)\">task</code> check, which runs before the generic path.</p>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"screen animate-in\">\n      <h2 class=\"screen-heading\">Parsing the token count safely</h2>\n      <p style=\"margin-bottom: var(--space-6);\">The compaction tool returns JSON, but the token count key isn't standardised. Three possible keys are tried in priority order:</p>\n      <div class=\"step-cards stagger-children\">\n        <div class=\"step-card animate-in\" style=\"--stagger-index: 0\">\n          <div class=\"step-num\">1</div>\n          <div class=\"step-body\">\n            <strong><code style=\"font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: var(--text-sm)\">tokens_remaining</code> — checked first</strong>\n            <p>The primary key. If present, its value is used — even if it's 0.</p>\n          </div>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"step-card animate-in\" style=\"--stagger-index: 1\">\n          <div class=\"step-num\">2</div>\n          <div class=\"step-body\">\n            <strong><code style=\"font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: var(--text-sm)\">token_count</code> — fallback</strong>\n            <p>Tried only if <code style=\"font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: var(--text-sm)\">tokens_remaining</code> is absent from the dict.</p>\n          </div>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"step-card animate-in\" style=\"--stagger-index: 2\">\n          <div class=\"step-num\">3</div>\n          <div class=\"step-body\">\n            <strong><code style=\"font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: var(--text-sm)\">remaining_tokens</code> — last resort</strong>\n            <p>If none of the keys are present, <code style=\"font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: var(--text-sm)\">token_count</code> defaults to 0. Non-JSON output also yields 0.</p>\n          </div>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"callout callout-accent\" style=\"margin-top: var(--space-4)\">\n        <div class=\"callout-icon\">⚠️</div>\n        <div class=\"callout-content\">\n          <strong class=\"callout-title\">Key presence, not truthiness</strong>\n          <p>The lookup uses a <code style=\"font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: var(--text-sm)\">for key in (...): if key in parsed: break</code> loop — not Python's <code style=\"font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: var(--text-sm)\">or</code> chaining. This ensures a value of <code style=\"font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: var(--text-sm)\">0</code> on the first key doesn't fall through to the second key (since <code style=\"font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: var(--text-sm)\">0 or ...</code> would be truthy-false and continue the chain).</p>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"screen animate-in\">\n      <h2 class=\"screen-heading\">Token percentage in the status bar</h2>\n      <p style=\"margin-bottom: var(--space-6);\">Once the context limit is known, the status bar shows both the absolute count <em>and</em> the percentage used:</p>\n      <div class=\"icon-rows\">\n        <div class=\"icon-row animate-in\">\n          <div class=\"icon-circle\" style=\"background: var(--color-text-secondary); font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: var(--text-sm); color: white\">12K</div>\n          <div>\n            <strong>Without context limit</strong>\n            <p>Shows <code style=\"font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: var(--text-sm)\">12.3K tokens</code> — just the count.</p>\n          </div>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"icon-row animate-in\">\n          <div class=\"icon-circle\" style=\"background: var(--color-actor-3); font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: var(--text-sm); color: white\">45%</div>\n          <div>\n            <strong>With context limit known</strong>\n            <p>Shows <code style=\"font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: var(--text-sm)\">12.3K (45%) tokens</code> — percentage helps you judge how close to the limit you are before compaction triggers.</p>\n          </div>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"icon-row animate-in\">\n          <div class=\"icon-circle\" style=\"background: var(--color-accent)\">📊</div>\n          <div>\n            <strong>Stored in SessionStats</strong>\n            <p><code style=\"font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: var(--text-sm)\">context_limit</code> and <code style=\"font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: var(--text-sm)\">context_compaction_count</code> are tracked across turns so you can see the full session history.</p>\n          </div>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"screen animate-in\">\n      <h2 class=\"screen-heading\">Quiz: Context management</h2>\n      <div class=\"quiz-container\" id=\"quiz-9\">\n        <div class=\"quiz-question-block\" data-question=\"q1\" data-correct=\"option-c\">\n          <h3 class=\"quiz-question\">The <code style=\"font-family: var(--font-mono)\">compact_conversation</code> tool's output JSON contains <code style=\"font-family: var(--font-mono)\">{\"tokens_remaining\": 0, \"token_count\": 9999}</code>. What token count does the TUI use?</h3>\n          <div class=\"quiz-options\">\n            <button class=\"quiz-option\" data-value=\"option-a\" onclick=\"selectOption(this)\">\n              <div class=\"quiz-option-radio\"></div>\n              <span>9999 — because 0 is falsy so the code falls through</span>\n            </button>\n            <button class=\"quiz-option\" data-value=\"option-b\" onclick=\"selectOption(this)\">\n              <div class=\"quiz-option-radio\"></div>\n              <span>9999 — token_count takes priority over tokens_remaining</span>\n            </button>\n            <button class=\"quiz-option\" data-value=\"option-c\" onclick=\"selectOption(this)\">\n              <div class=\"quiz-option-radio\"></div>\n              <span>0 — tokens_remaining is present in the dict so its value is used, even though it's 0</span>\n            </button>\n          </div>\n          <div class=\"quiz-feedback\" id=\"q1-feedback-9\"></div>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"quiz-question-block\" data-question=\"q2\" data-correct=\"option-b\">\n          <h3 class=\"quiz-question\">When does the TUI show a percentage next to the token count (e.g. \"12.3K (45%) tokens\")?</h3>\n          <div class=\"quiz-options\">\n            <button class=\"quiz-option\" data-value=\"option-a\" onclick=\"selectOption(this)\">\n              <div class=\"quiz-option-radio\"></div>\n              <span>Always — the percentage is always computed</span>\n            </button>\n            <button class=\"quiz-option\" data-value=\"option-b\" onclick=\"selectOption(this)\">\n              <div class=\"quiz-option-radio\"></div>\n              <span>Only when a context limit has been set via <code style=\"font-family: var(--font-mono)\">set_context_limit()</code></span>\n            </button>\n            <button class=\"quiz-option\" data-value=\"option-c\" onclick=\"selectOption(this)\">\n              <div class=\"quiz-option-radio\"></div>\n              <span>Only after context has been compacted at least once</span>\n            </button>\n          </div>\n          <div class=\"quiz-feedback\" id=\"q2-feedback-9\"></div>\n        </div>\n        <button class=\"quiz-check-btn\" onclick=\"checkQuiz('quiz-9')\">Check Answers</button>\n        <button class=\"quiz-reset-btn\" onclick=\"resetQuiz('quiz-9')\">Try Again</button>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"screen animate-in\">\n      <div class=\"callout callout-accent\">\n        <div class=\"callout-icon\">🎓</div>\n        <div class=\"callout-content\">\n          <strong class=\"callout-title\">You've completed the full course!</strong>\n          <p>From the approval system to web search, subagent delegation, and context management — you now understand how agent-tui extends a basic TUI into a full agent interface. The patterns repeat: intercept special tool names early, emit semantic events, keep the UI layer thin. Build on these three rules and you can add any capability.</p>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n</section>\n\n<script>\n// ==================== Tooltip System ====================",
